<html id="a9516f2dfaa87f82516b4a3f92659928968cdd72" class="StudioLegacy Legacy" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" lang="en-US" xml:lang="en-US">
<head><title>
	Aflac Incorporated - Aflac Incorporated Announces First Quarter 2026 Results
</title><meta content="text/html; charset=UTF-8" http-equiv="Content-type" /><meta content="RevealTrans(Duration=0,Transition=0)" http-equiv="Page-Enter" /><meta content="IE=edge,chrome=1" http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" /><meta content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" name="viewport" /><meta content="KvO0bE72yqR9SVhkyUtaLPB2nN6KGmV9thYponV6vpk" name="google-site-verification" /><meta content="Aflac Incorporated Announces First Quarter 2026 Results" property="og:title" /><meta name="description" content="Aflac Incorporated (NYSE: AFL) today reported its first quarter results. For the Quarter Total revenues were $4.3 billion , which was a 27.9% increase year over year. Net earnings were $1.0 billion, or $1.98 per diluted share, compared with $29 million, or $0.05 per diluted share a year ago. Adjusted earnings* were $901 million, compared with $906 million a year ago, reflecting a decrease of 0.6%. Adjusted earnings per diluted share* increased 5.4% to $1.75. The annualized return on average shareholders&#39; equity was 13.7%. The annualized adjusted return on equity excluding foreign currency remeasurement* was 16.4%. The company returned $1.3 billion to shareholders, consisting of $1.0 billion in share repurchase and $315 million in dividends. Commenting on the company&#39;s results, Aflac Incorporated Chairman and Chief Executive Officer Daniel P. Amos stated: &quot;Aflac delivered solid earnings for the quarter. These results reflect our focused execution of our strategy and thus creating" property="og:description" /><meta content="https://mma.prnewswire.com/media/1135887/Aflac_Incorporated_Logo.jpg" property="og:image" /><meta content="website" property="og:type" /><meta content="https://investors.aflac.com/press-releases/press-release-details/2026/Aflac-Incorporated-Announces-First-Quarter-2026-Results/default.aspx" property="og:url" /><meta content="400" property="og:image:width" /><meta content="186" property="og:image:height" /><meta name="twitter:title" content="Aflac Incorporated Announces First Quarter 2026 Results" /><meta name="twitter:description" content="Aflac Incorporated (NYSE: AFL) today reported its first quarter results. For the Quarter Total revenues were $4.3 billion , which was a 27.9% increase year over year. Net earnings were $1.0 billion, or $1.98 per diluted share, compared with $29 million, or $0.05 per diluted share a year ago. Adjusted earnings* were $901 million, compared with $906 million a year ago, reflecting a decrease of 0.6%. Adjusted earnings per diluted share* increased 5.4% to $1.75. The annualized return on average shareholders&#39; equity was 13.7%. The annualized adjusted return on equity excluding foreign currency remeasurement* was 16.4%. The company returned $1.3 billion to shareholders, consisting of $1.0 billion in share repurchase and $315 million in dividends. Commenting on the company&#39;s results, Aflac Incorporated Chairman and Chief Executive Officer Daniel P. Amos stated: &quot;Aflac delivered solid earnings for the quarter. These results reflect our focused execution of our strategy and thus creating" /><meta name="twitter:image" content="https://mma.prnewswire.com/media/1135887/Aflac_Incorporated_Logo.jpg" /><!--[if lte IE 8]>
